ocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":21,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":30,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":65,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705190,"age":96,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Agnes de Snitterton was born about 1194, in England. S